Vice President Kamala Harris spoke at the Chief of Mission Residence in Tokyo, Japan, emphasizing the longstanding and enduring economic partnership between the United States and Japan. She highlighted the CHIPS Act as a demonstration of the commitment to invest in innovation and research and development. The act aims to boost semiconductor manufacturing in the US, lower costs of everyday products, create good-paying union jobs, and increase investment in innovation and new technologies. Harris emphasized the importance of diversifying the supply chain and coordinating with allies like Japan. She also acknowledged the need for resilient supply chains and forward-looking innovation, especially in light of the weaknesses exposed by the pandemic. Harris expressed gratitude for the opportunity to have a direct conversation and provide helpful information to the leaders present, reinforcing the alliance between the US and Japan and the shared goal of inclusive economic growth and resilience.